### T27 — Reversed transaction — Reliability
POST http://localhost:8001/analyze-ticket
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticket_id": "TKT-EDGE-004",
  "complaint": "I sent 5000 taka to wrong number",
  "transaction_history": [
    {"transaction_id": "TXN-REV", "timestamp": "2026-04-14T14:00:00Z", "type": "transfer", "amount": 5000, "counterparty": "+8801799999", "status": "reversed"}
  ]
}

# Discussion: when amount matches but status=reversed, what verdict?
# - status_contradiction: complaint does not say "failed", tx status is
#   "reversed" (not "completed" or "failed") → no contradiction detected by
#   current rules.
# - Likely verdict: "consistent" because the transfer happened and was
#   subsequently reversed. The customer may or may not have been notified.
# Expected: relevant_transaction_id=TXN-REV, evidence_verdict=consistent
#           (or insufficient_data if LLM is conservative), case_type=wrong_transfer,
#           severity=high, department=dispute_resolution, human_review=true

###

